        <abstract> 
<p>Criticises Herbert Spencer’s <hi rend="italic">Principles of sociology</hi>, particularly for its treatment of the family, for its superficiality, and for its dependence on J. F. McLennan’s views on exogamy. Americans are coming to see Spencer’s ideas as too broad.</p> 
